Implement a react application that allows users to create, modify, delete recipes.
The user should have a profile that includes a picture they can upload, their email address, and their name.
Recipes should be tied to a user.
There should be an option for a recipe to be public or private.
Users should be able to browser their recipes.
User authentication should be passwordless and be handled by SuperTokens.
The authentication should be a custom client for supertokens.
For binary data and images, use MinIO.
Make sure that all actions are confirmed that a user is logged in.
Use a MERN stack for the solution
The client actions should be separated from the server actions via an express api middleware.
All server application actions should be logged to loki/grafana.
All client application actions should be logged to loki/grafana with the sessions uniquely identified by the user's email address.
The server application should be written in typescript, whereever possible.  Only exclude typescript when it is not possible.
The website should utilize MaterialUI for the UI for the client.
The solution should utililze Docker images for all of the services identified in the requirements.
The solution should utilize Docker Compose for the orchestration of the services.
While we are not utilizing kubernetes immediately, the solution should not do anything that would prevent it from being used in the future.
The website should follow the best practices for web development.
The website should have have a home page that describes the website, using images and text.
The website should have a top navigation bar.
The website should have a footer.
The website should be viewable on mobile and desktop devices in a form factor that is comfortable for the device in use.

## Additional Requirements (Clarifications):

### Recipe Schema:
- Title (required)
- Description (required)
- Ingredients: array of objects with quantity, unit, and name
- Instructions: sequential array where each step may optionally have an associated image
- Tags: array of strings for categorization
- Images: recipes support multiple images (stored in MinIO)
- Created/modified timestamps
- Public/private flag
- Owner user reference

### Search and Filter:
- Users can search recipes by title, description, ingredients, and tags
- Filtering should be granular and allow searching on specific recipe elements

### Authentication:
- Passwordless authentication using OTP (One-Time Password)
- Custom SuperTokens UI (not the default interface)
- Email-based OTP delivery

### Logging:
- Configurable logging levels (default: info level)
- Log both successful and unsuccessful actions
- Include sufficient data for problem reproduction
- Client logs identified by user email
- Server logs for all API actions

### MinIO Configuration:
- Store profile pictures, recipe images, and all website image content
- File upload limit: 1MB (configurable)
- Support for multiple image formats

### Environment Configuration:
- Separate docker-compose files for development and production
- Infrastructure supports multiple environments
- Initial implementation: development environment only
- Environment-specific configuration files

### Content:
- Home page with placeholder content and images
- Print-friendly recipe view
- No import/export functionality in initial version

### Recipe Browsing & Discovery:
- Users can browse OTHER users' public recipes via "Explore Recipes" page
- "My Recipes" page shows only user's own recipes (public and private)
- Public recipes have shareable URLs
- Search requires authentication

### Recipe Images:
- Multiple images can be uploaded per recipe
- First image serves as cover/primary image
- Each instruction step may optionally have an associated image

### Tags & Units:
- Tags: Free-form text entry with autocomplete suggestions from existing tags in database
- Measurement Units: Predefined list (cup, tbsp, tsp, oz, lb, g, kg, ml, l, piece, to taste) with "other" option for free text

### Authentication UI Requirements:
- Custom Material-UI authentication pages (no pre-built SuperTokens UI)
- Registration/Login flow using OTP via email
- Email prefix used as default user name (editable in profile later)
- SuperTokens handles email delivery
- Post-login redirect to Dashboard page
- First-time user welcome modal with site overview (content TBD)
- Error handling via Material-UI Snackbar notifications
- Loading states during OTP verification
